@prefix : <http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/pe#> .
@prefix ce: <http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/ce#> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#> .
@prefix tbox: <http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox#> .
@prefix foaf: <http://xmlns.com/foaf/0.1/> .

<http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/pe> a owl:Ontology ;
    :profilingPolicy """
Programming-language profiling uses only native support and standard-library support.
Refined concepts are asserted selectively rather than exhaustively.
No support is recorded for mere encodings or otherwise insignificant realizations.
Refined support is not inherited automatically from coarse support.
Support assertions are qualified only when especially representative or potentially ambiguous.
Borderline cases may be documented using skos:note.
Paradigm-based subclassing of programming languages is not used; paradigms are represented via concept support.
"""@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Sub-ontology / ABox for programming-language concepts and programming languages"@en ;
    owl:imports <http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/ce>,
        <http://www.softlang.org/ontologies/tbox> .

:Ada a :ProgrammingLanguage,
        tbox:LanguageEntity,
        owl:NamedIndividual ;
    rdfs:label "Ada"@en ;
    ce:nativelySupports ce:DataAbstraction,
        ce:Exceptions,
        ce:ImperativeParadigm,
        ce:ProceduralAbstraction,
        ce:SharedMemoryConcurrency,
        ce:StaticTyping,
        ce:StrongTyping,
        ce:TaskParallelism ;
    tbox:hasArea ce:PLT,
        ce:SE,
        ce:SLE ;
    tbox:hasSpace ce:Programware ;
    rdfs:comment "statically typed language with strong support for reliability and concurrency"@en ;
    foaf:page <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ada_(programming_language)> ;
    foaf:isPrimaryTopicOf <https://dbpedia.org/resource/Ada_(programming_language)> .

